        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>124600</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig><choice><unclear>α</unclear><unclear>λ</unclear></choice>
                    <choice><unclear>ι</unclear><unclear>τ</unclear></choice><choice><unclear>ω</unclear><unclear>ξ</unclear></choice></orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <w lemma="δεκάτα">δεκά<supplied reason="lost">ταν</supplied></w> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> dîme.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> tithe.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> decima.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>At line 1, the orientation of the serif of the third letter allows only for a <foreign xml:lang="">Ξ</foreign> or a <foreign xml:lang="">Ω</foreign>; 
                    so the most plausible reading of the segment seems to be either -<foreign xml:lang="">αιω</foreign> or -<foreign xml:lang="">ατω</foreign>.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
